{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"322","heading":"Petitions","label":"322 Petitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t35/ptIII/ch32","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft35%2Fs322","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection effective upon the expiration of the 1-year period beginning , and applicable only to patents described in ( note), with certain exceptions and limitations, see section 6(f)(2), (3) of , set out as a note under .Sept. 16, 2011section 3(n)(1) of Pub. L. 112–2935 U.S.C. 100Pub. L. 112–29section 321 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Requirements of Petition","label":"a .—Requirements of Petition","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft35%2Fs322%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft35%2Fs322%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the petition is accompanied by payment of the fee established by the Director under section 321;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft35%2Fs322%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the petition identifies all real parties in interest;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft35%2Fs322%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft35%2Fs322%2Fa%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"copies of patents and printed publications that the petitioner relies upon in support of the petition; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft35%2Fs322%2Fa%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"affidavits or declarations of supporting evidence and opinions, if the petitioner relies on other factual evidence or on expert opinions;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft35%2Fs322%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the petition provides such other information as the Director may require by regulation; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft35%2Fs322%2Fa%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the petitioner provides copies of any of the documents required under paragraphs (2), (3), and (4) to the patent owner or, if applicable, the designated representative of the patent owner.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Public Availability","label":"b .—Public Availability","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t35/s322","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft35%2Fs322%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"As soon as practicable after the receipt of a petition under section 321, the Director shall make the petition available to the public.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
